	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64397612"><p>(To be clear on terminology: colony != reef. A coral colony is a cluster of polyps that bud or divide off from each other, all genetically identical and interconnected by the coenosarc to share resources, with each polyp living for a few years.  For a plant analogy, the colony would be a a tree, and the polyps, individual leaves of that tree)</p></div>
	</div>

